japanese: あの ひと あの かた
reading: あの ひと あの かた
meaning: That person, he, she (あの　かた　is the polite equivalent of あの　ひと）

japanese: ［どうぞ］ よろしく ［お願いします］。
reading: ［どうぞ］ よろしく ［お願いします］。
meaning: Pleased to meet you. (lit. Please be nice to me. Usually used at the end of a self-introduction.)

examples.japanese: ［どうぞ］　よろしく　［お 願[ねが]いします］。

meaning: Excuse me, but (used when asking someone for personal information such as their name or address)
